The brother of the Minister of Agriculture, Sabo Nanono has been abducted by unidentified gunmen. The criminals stormed the ministerâ€™s home in Tofai Village, Gabasawa Local Government Area in Kano State from where, Babawuro Nanono, was taken. Nanono who is the Minister of Agriculture also serves as the Sarkin Fulani of Tofai Village. Reports say the gunmen arrived in large numbers in the early hours of Monday. Reasons for the attack was yet to be ascertained as at the time of filing this report. Confirming the incident, the spokesperson of the Kano State Police Command, DSP Abdullahi Haruna, said the police are investigating the matter.